cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision using event cameras, which are commonly used in robotics applications. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a new method for computing convolutions, which involves updating an internal state asynchronously, making it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper demonstrates the application of the proposed method to corner detection, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
